doc.after: The 2010 United States Census[81] reported that Los Angeles had a population of 3,792,621.[82] The population density was 8,092.3 people per square mile (2,913.0/kmÂ²). The age distribution was 874,525 people (23.1%) under 18, 434,478 people (11.5%) from 18 to 24, 1,209,367 people (31.9%) from 25 to 44, 877,555 people (23.1%) from 45 to 64, and 396,696 people (10.5%) who were 65 or older.[82] The median age was 34.1 years. For every 100 females there were 99.2 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 97.6 males.[82]
